description:
## Goal
Extract HTTP server code from main.rs to http.rs, deduplicate response helpers, and add unit tests.

## Why
- main.rs is 2,289 lines - HTTP server is the cleanest piece to extract
- CORS header code is duplicated 8+ times
- No tests exist for HTTP layer - adding them prevents regressions

## Files
- `server/launcher/src/main.rs` - Remove ~240 lines
- `server/launcher/src/http.rs` - New file (~200 lines with tests)

## What moves to http.rs

### Functions to move:
- `run_http_server()` (lines 2017-2057)
- `handle_http_request()` (lines 2060-2189)
- `send_command()` (lines 2192-2241)
- `send_lsp_payload()` (lines 2007-2013)

### New helpers to create:
```rust
fn cors_headers() -> Vec<tiny_http::Header> { ... }
fn json_response(body: &str, status: u16) -> Response<...> { ... }
fn json_response_with_cors(body: &str, status: u16) -> Response<...> { ... }
fn error_response(msg: &str, status: u16) -> Response<...> { ... }
```

## What stays in main.rs
- `next_lsp_request_id()` and `NEXT_LSP_REQUEST_ID` static
- `create_execute_command_request()` (used elsewhere too)

## Dependencies http.rs needs
```rust
use crate::{next_lsp_request_id, create_execute_command_request, verbose_logging_enabled};
```

## Unit tests to add

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;

    #[test]
    fn test_cors_headers_includes_required_headers() {
        let headers = cors_headers();
        // Verify Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_json_response_sets_content_type() {
        let resp = json_response(r#"{"ok":true}"#, 200);
        // Verify Content-Type: application/json
        // Verify status code
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_json_response_with_cors_includes_cors_headers() {
        let resp = json_response_with_cors(r#"{"ok":true}"#, 200);
        // Verify both JSON content type and CORS headers
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_error_response_format() {
        let resp = error_response("something broke", 500);
        // Verify body is {"error":"something broke"}
        // Verify status 500
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `cargo build` succeeds
- [ ] `cargo test` passes (new tests + any existing)
- [ ] `cargo clippy` has no new warnings
- [ ] HTTP endpoints work: /eval, /health, /stop, /boot, /recompile, /quit
- [ ] CORS preflight (OPTIONS) still works
- [ ] No behavior change

## Definition of Done
- main.rs is ~240 lines shorter
- http.rs exists with:
  - Extracted HTTP server functions
  - Deduplicated response helpers (4 new functions)
  - Unit tests for all helpers (4+ tests)
- Manual verification: `curl http://localhost:57130/health` returns `{"status":"ok"}`

## Estimated effort
~45 minutes
